				\begin{document}$$ \gamma_{{{\text{sub}}}} + Q_{e} = \gamma_{{{\text{Zn}}}} $$\end{document}where Qe stems from the partial energy of the electric field. The smaller γsub becomes, the larger Qe shall be needed, then leading to a more significant trend of dendrite growth. By transforming 2D nanosheets with large specific surface areas and abundant surface chemistry into an anode protective layer, it’s easy to get a high surface energy substrate to deal with the dendrite growth issue.
